me  Disability and Human Development  Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19) Guidance and Resources      Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19) Guidance and Resources  COVID-19 resources for people with disabilities, their families, service providers and the workforce that supports them.  This list of resources have been compiled to help people with disabilities, their families, service providers and the workforce that supports them have access to the latest information about COVID-19.      Engagement opportunities for people with disabilities and their families   Updated May 8, 2020  IDHD/DHD faculty launch the project “Map your COVID-19 Disability Experience”. Please share your story by June 30, 2020.  Volunteer for Chicagoland COVID-19 opportunities (remote & in person)  Prepare for Hospitalization during COVID-19:  A Checklist for People with Disabilities  Order a face mask that gives lip reading ability to the deaf and hard of hearing  Stories needed about impact of COVID-19 on people with disabilities  Masks for the Disability Community  Special Olympics School for Strength Online exercise      Education materials for people with disabilities and their families   Updated May 8, 2020  The Chicagoland Disabled People of Color Coalition and the Illinois Self-Advocacy Alliance, Inc.  Illinois Statewide COVID-19 Resource List for People with Disabilities in Marginalized Communities  Guía de Recursos COVID-19 para Personas Discapacitadas en Comunidades Marginadas de Illinois  Access to Respite Care and Help (ARCH) National Respite Network & Resource Center  COVID-19 Respite and Caregiving Resources  Online Respite Opportunities and Options  Families Together Inc.  Navigating COVID-19 When Your Child/Youth has a Disability (resources by disability type)  Autism Research Institute Autism & COVID-19 Webinar Recordings:  Anxiety, Autism: Five Prime Suspects – with tips for coping at home during the Coronavirus outbreak  Emotional Support for Families during COVID-19  Support for Indivi